==English==
====Etymology====
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[δραστικός]]''' ''(drasticos'') "[[active]], efficient, (also as a medical term: [[drastic]])" < '''[[δράσις]]''' (''drasis'') "strength, efficacy" < '''[[δράω]]''' (''drao'') "to do".

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æstɪk|-æstɪk]]

===Adjective===
'''drastic'''
# [[extreme]], [[severe]]

